3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a framework to improve the accuracy of optical flow algorithms.
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper deals with tracking non-rigid objects, which is a fundamental research issue in robotics.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with improving the accuracy of optical flow algorithms, which are commonly used in multimedia applications.
